e does she suspect that her search for justice will land her in the arms of wealthy English gentleman, Jordan Tavistock. As Clea and Jordan\'s attraction grows, so does the danger. Now their biggest concern isn\'t whether a proper gentleman and a cat burglar can find happinessit\'s whether they\'ll survive long enough to find out.','HarperCollins Australia','2011-07-01','http://books.google.com/books?id=12kDZfK49_4C&dq=keeper+of+the+bride+tess&hl=&cd=5&source=gbs_api','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=12kDZfK49_4C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','12kDZfK49_4C','PHY',NULL,1,2),(17,'Presumed Guilty','Not Present','Not Present','2007-01-01','http://books.google.com/books?id=A3B6AAAACAAJ&dq=presumed+guilty+tess&hl=&cd=3&source=gbs_api','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=A3B6AAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','A3B6AAAACAAJ','PHY',NULL,1,NULL),(18,'The Apprentice','Jane Rizzoli and Maura Isles—the inspiration for the hit TNT series—continue their crime-solving streak. The bestselling author of The Surgeon returns—and so does that chilling novel’s diabolical villain. Though held behind bars, Warren Hoyt still haunts a helpless city, seeming to bequeath his evil legacy to a student all-too-diligent . . . and all-too-deadly. It is a boiling hot Boston summer. Adding to the city’s woes is a series of shocking crimes, in which wealthy men are made to watch while their wives are brutalized. A sadistic demand that ends in abduction and death. The pattern suggests one man: serial killer Warren Hoyt, recently removed from the city’s streets. Police can only assume an acolyte is at large, a maniac basing his attacks on the twisted medical techniques of the madman he so admires. At least that’s what Detective Jane Rizzoli thinks. Forced again to confront the killer who scarred her—literally and figuratively—she is determined to finally end Hoyt’s awful influence . . . even if it means receiving more resistance from her all-male 